"{\"uid\": \"express.co.uk-sport-othersport-1931512-olympics-official-has-accreditation-revoked\", \"text\": \"    The behaviour was reportedly the subject of a complaint from a Brazilian journalist, who passed the information onto organisers. He alleged the male appeared to be watching himself on the big screens before making the gesture.  He first made it when Australian Chloe Covell was in action. Minutes later, he repeated the gesture when he was stationed close to Japanese athlete Liz Akama.  The controversy cameamid a gripping final, with Coco Yoshizawa of Japan producing a thrilling display to take gold. Compatriot Liz Akama earned silver, and Rayssa Leal of Brazil bronze.  We use your sign-up to provide content in ways you have consented to and to improve our understanding of you. This may include adverts from us and 3rd parties based on our understanding. You can unsubscribe at any time. Read ourPrivacy Policy  Do not miss:Show your colours and get Team GB's official kit for the Paris Olympics  Do not miss:Olympics judo star immediately disqualified after 'scandalous' attack on hero  Do not miss:Boxer at centre of gender row along with Khelif one win away from Olympics medal  Discovery+is the new home of the Olympics. The streamer is set to broadcast 3,800 hours of sport live from Paris.  Sports fans can getDiscovery+ for \\u00a33.99a month until the end of 2024 via Amazon Prime's video channels. This also comes with anAmazon Prime 30-day free trial.  The 14-year-old led the field during qualifying with a combined score of 258.92. And she cemented glory in the final by pulling off a bigspin flip with a boardslide to send the crowd into raptures.  SEARCH  CONNECT WITH US  TODAY'S PAPER  See today's front and back pages, download the newspaper, order back issues and use the historic Daily Express newspaper archive.  EXPRESS.CO.UK  Daily Express uses notifications to keep you updated\"}"